'''New York State Route 167''' is a [[state highway]] in New York, running from the [[Otsego County, New York|Otsego County]] village of [[Richfield Springs, New York|Richfield Springs]] to the [[Herkimer County, New York|Herkimer County]] village of [[Dolgeville, New York|Dolgeville]].

NY 169 begins as Church Street in Richfield Springs. As it leaves the village, it enters Herkimer County for the balance of its route.

A two-lane highway its entire length, NY 167 is narrow and winding through southern Herkimer County. It crosses [[New York State Route 168|NY 168]] diagonally in [[Paines Hollow, New York|Paines Hollow]] and has a brief duplex with [[New York State Route 5S|NY 5S]].

In [[Little Falls (city), New York|Little Falls]], NY 167 crosses the [[Mohawk River]]/[[Erie Canal]], then uses Albany Street for one block, then South Ann Street in a southerly direction, to meet [[New York State Route 5|NY 5]], turning left to join it in a duplex. At the Albany Street/South Ann Street intersection, Northbound NY 167 abuts Southbound [[New York State Route 169|NY 169]] which uses the same intersection without crossing. Southbound, NY 167 leaves NY 5 west of the overpass, looping backward on Albany Street and then turning right across the river. With NY 5, NY 167 forms a quarter mile, wrong-way triplex with NY 169 on the eastern edge of town. After the duplex, NY 167 turns left, heading uphill before leaving the city.

NY 167 then follows a winding path along the [[West Canada Creek]] on the eastern edge of Herkimer County, ending in [[Dolgeville, New York|Dolgeville]] at [[New York State Route 29|NY 29]].

==Communities along the route==
*[[Richfield Springs, New York|Richfield Springs]]
*[[Cullen, New York|Cullen]]
*[[Jordanville, New York|Jordanville]]
*[[Paines Hollow, New York|Paines Hollow]]
*[[Little Falls (city), New York|Little Falls]]
*[[Dolgeville, New York|Dolgeville]]

